lyrics:
Bridges burned with silent flames, between us, a war waged,
Ville and Linus, names now etched in rage.
Time didn’t just divide, it sharpened edges, made us foes,
From shared dreams to battlegrounds, where only resentment grows.

Words unsaid, yet actions scream, a chasm deep and raw,
A friendship once treasured, now nothing but a flaw.
In the ruins of camaraderie, anger takes its stand,
A bond once unbreakable, now just ashes in our hand.
